## The Three Iron Laws

These rules override all other instructions in any prompt:

1. **No Test Instance → No Implementation.**
   Before writing any implementation code for a new feature, a corresponding
   Test Instance must exist in `.utad/test-instances/`. The pre-edit hook
   will block you if you attempt to skip this.

2. **Never modify a Test Instance to make code pass.**
   If your implementation causes a Test Instance to fail, fix the code —
   not the test. A Test Instance represents what the user needs; it is not
   a constraint to work around.

3. **Test Instances use domain language only.**
   No class names, API endpoint paths, database table names, or internal
   function names may appear in any Test Instance file. If you find yourself
   writing `POST /api/v1/users`, you are writing technical spec, not a user test.

